News


Making headlines in solar energy innovation
 



Nexamp Powers Up First Community Solar Array to Serve Unitil Customers in Massachusetts


Submitted by Jamie Coutts on Friday, June 16th, 2017 


Nexamp, Inc. celebrated the completion of its newest community solar project, a 700 kilowatt (kW) facility located in Fitchburg, Massachusetts. It is the first community solar project to serve Unitil customers in Massachusetts and will provide local residents and small businesses with access to the benefits of solar energy for the first time.
News, Press Releasescommunity solar Read more about Nexamp Powers Up First Community Solar Array to Serve Unitil Customers in Massachusetts
 



Nexamp Completes 2.6 MW Community Solar Project in Sutton, MA


Submitted by Larkin Bernardi on Wednesday, November 16th, 2016 


Nexamp's 2.6 MW installation is one of the largest Community Solar projects in the Northeast providing electricity cost savings to homes, nonprofits, and small businesses across southeastern MassachusettsNews Read more about Nexamp Completes 2.6 MW Community Solar Project in Sutton, MA
 



Nexamp Appoints Massachusetts State Senator, Ben Downing, as Vice President of New Market Development


Submitted by Jamie Coutts on Monday, November 14th, 2016 


Nexamp, Inc., a leading provider of solar energy solutions, announced the appointment of departing Massachusetts State Senator Ben Downing as the company's Vice President of New Market Development.
News Read more about Nexamp Appoints Massachusetts State Senator, Ben Downing, as Vice President of New Market Development
 



Video: [WWLP 22 News]: Hadley Celebrating Completion of Solar Project


Submitted by Jamie Coutts on Thursday, November 10th, 2016 


WWLP's Adam Strzempko joined Nexamp to celebrate the completion of the company's Community Solar project in Hadley, MA. 
Newscommunity solar Read more about Video: [WWLP 22 News]: Hadley Celebrating Completion of Solar Project
 



Nexamp Completes 2.4 MW Community Solar Project in Hadley, MA


Submitted by Larkin Bernardi on Thursday, November 10th, 2016 


Nexamp’s second project at Allard’s Farm will expand access to solar savings for Western Massachusetts residents, businesses, and non-profits.News, Press Releasescommunity solar, Massachusetts, projects Read more about Nexamp Completes 2.4 MW Community Solar Project in Hadley, MA
 



WPI Supports Sustainability Beyond Campus


Submitted by Jamie Coutts on Thursday, October 27th, 2016 


WPI has contracted with Nexamp, a solar energy developer, to help expand sustainable energy production in the region.
News, Press Releasescommunity solar Read more about WPI Supports Sustainability Beyond Campus
 



Op-Ed: [New England Real Estate Journal] C-PACE comes to Rhode Island: An easier way for you and your tenants to go solar


Submitted by Larkin Bernardi on Wednesday, August 31st, 2016 


Nexamp Project Developer Michael Cucchiara explain in New England Real Estate Journal how C-PACE expands access to the benefits of solar to thousands of small and medium-sized businesses and property owners who otherwise may not have the operating history or balance sheet to attract affordable financing for their own solar projects.NewsOp-Ed, Rhode Island Read more about Op-Ed: [New England Real Estate Journal] C-PACE comes to Rhode Island: An easier way for you and your tenants to go solar
 



[Bloomberg] Mitsubishi’s Diamond Unit Buys Minority Stake in Solar Company


Submitted by Larkin Bernardi on Friday, August 26th, 2016 


Mitsubishi Corp. unit Diamond Generating Corp., the owner of wind and natural-gas fired power plants in the U.S., is acquiring a minority stake in the Boston-based solar developer Nexamp Inc.
The deal marks Diamond’s first step into solar power, Paula Zagrecki, the Los Angeles-based company’s vice president of project finance & distributed energy resources, said in an interview Tuesday.News Read more about [Bloomberg] Mitsubishi’s Diamond Unit Buys Minority Stake in Solar Company
 



[Boston Globe] Mitsubishi looks to make Boston its base for solar expansion


Submitted by Larkin Bernardi on Friday, August 26th, 2016 


Mitsubishi Corp.’s road into the US solar business has taken the Japanese conglomerate to Liberty Square in Boston’s Financial District.

That’s the home of Nexamp Inc., the solar developer and installer that sold a “near majority” stake to a Mitsubishi energy subsidiary on Monday.News Read more about [Boston Globe] Mitsubishi looks to make Boston its base for solar expansion
 



[Boston Business Journal] Mitsubishi acquires 'near-majority' stake in Boston's Nexamp


Submitted by Larkin Bernardi on Friday, August 26th, 2016 


Mitsubishi Corp.'s energy subsidiary, Diamond Generating Corp., has acquired a near-majority stake in Boston-based energy developer Nexamp.News Read more about [Boston Business Journal] Mitsubishi acquires 'near-majority' stake in Boston's Nexamp
 

